HAMAM SERIES IS BACK!!

Join us for another night of rare grooves, psychedelic disco thrillers and many other delights at the one and only Nublu.

Afyonbando (Emre Garan) will be on the decks with guest DJ Memos (Serhan Aydemir) giving us straight up ottoman disco business strictly from the vaults.

Sick visuals and spectacles all night by Selin Bonfil & co.

AFYONBANDO ////// MEMOS

https://soundcloud.com/emregaran

https://soundcloud.com/memosmusic

***MEMOS

A music lover from the start, MEMOS (Serhan Aydemir) first began collecting cassette tapes in the late ’80s. Over the years, he channeled all his energy toward this passion, constantly discovering new music styles. By the mid-90s, he became a radio host in his hometown of Istanbul before launching his own show on the premier electronic/indie station Dinamo.fm.

Today, the Brooklyn-based DJ/producer continues to share weekly mixes with fans and listeners on Dinamo by day and manning the decks at some of NYC’s most popular venues.

***AFYONBANDO

NYC and Istanbul based DJ Afyonbando a.k.a. Emre Garan is known best for his blend of styles, he plays anything as long as its got some soul. Bringing in multi-cultural sounds that range from psychedelic disco thrillers to minimal and afro funk , he keeps the vibes right day and night.

He has played at many international festivals and venues at a very young age. Having started his very first radio show at age 13 , he has shared the stage with the likes of Soul Clap, Acid Pauli, Nicolas Jaar, Kyodai and Istanbul's local giants such as Baris K and Kaan Duzarat.

Doors open at 7pm. Jamie Kent starts the show at 8pm!

Paul Thorn has created an innovative and impressive career, pleasing crowds with his muscular brand of roots music – bluesy, rocking and thoroughly Southern American, yet also speaking universal truths. Among those who value originality, inspiration, eccentricity and character – as well as talent that hovers somewhere on the outskirts of genius, the story of Paul Thorn is already familiar. Raised in Tupelo, Mississippi, among the same spirits (and some of the actual people) who nurtured the young Elvis generations before, Paul Thorn has rambled down back roads and jumped out of airplanes, worked for years in a furniture factory, battled four-time world champion boxer Roberto Duran on national television, signed with and been dropped by a major label, performed on stages with Bonnie Raitt, Mark Knopfler, Sting, and John Prine among many others, and made some of the most emotionally restless yet fully accessible music of our time.

He’s also appeared on major television shows such as Late Night with Conan O’Brien and Jimmy Kimmel Live, been the subject of numerous National Public Radio (NPR) features and charted multiple times on the Billboard Top 100 and Americana Radioi Charts.

This year, Paul will be releasing an album titled Don’t Let the Devil Ride, which he describes as “the culmination of my whole life in music, coming back to my roots.” It marks his first time recording gospel music - featuring guests such as the Blind Boys of Alabama, the McCrary Sisters, and Preservation Hall Horns - and his creation of a body of strikingly original songs that address the foibles of human relationships without necessarily favoring the sacred over the profane.

About the opener, Neal McCarthy: 

Neal is a local legend logging over 20 years in the local scene playing all over New England. He is equally adept at rock, blues, and country.

Kick off your weekend with FREE live music in the RME Courtyard! Live@Five is totally free, for all ages, and features the best local bands to come rock out for everyone to enjoy.

The Velies is a band based in the Quad Cities, USA featuring local music veterans Tom Swanson, Mo Carter, Marty Reyhons, and Aaron Jorgenson.  The band writes, records, and performs introspective original music. They rely on the organic sound of acoustic and electric guitars, bass, ukulele, and drums, as the bed for rustic vocal harmonies, creating bittersweet meandering songs with urgent undercurrents. Swanson and Carter share lead vocal duties while all members lend supporting roles in that department, often intertwining parts. The Velies perform for audiences of all sizes in the Quad Cities and the surrounding areas, from intimate clubs to festival stages.

event.description: Doors at 7pm. An albums undertaking can be an explosion or a slow burn. I spent almost five years creating, recording, arranging and performing the music on this record. Hundreds of hours were spent riding the bus to Clackamas Community College to access their wonderful recording tools and work with the amazing Sacha Müller. Over the years, I used Portlands incredible studios to record my talented friends, including the inspiring Esperanza Spalding. They dusted their magic on these songs; songs about women in my life like my beloved Grandma Mac on the cover, and songs for all the versions of myself that live in my head and heart, maturing and developing with each year of this project. This rare orchestral presentation is a dream come true, made possible through a RACC grant. It let me enlist a brass quartet, string trio and choir to bring the albums recorded textures to life. In a studio, anything is possible. You can create four-part french horn harmonies and play them all yourself (like I did) or sing an entire chorale (ditto). Now, 17 other musicians will come together on-stage to make my recordings a sonic reality. It means so much to be able to share this with you. This performance is made possible through a generous grant from the RACC. To listen to early releases from Women in My Head, find/follow Megan Diana on iTunes and Spotify. Nightride, the most recent release featuring Esperanza Spalding on bass, is track #1 for this years PDX POP NOW! compilation.

Born in Dallas Texas Gary began playing guitar at age 10,soon after writing songs. Myrick by 18 writing his all original songs and sound in Dallas clubs soon playiing north Texas in his band Gary Myrick & Slip of the Wrist.After being asked to move to Austin by Blues great Uncle John Turner Myrick replaced Stevie Ray Vaughn in Austin band Krackerjack after they had fired Stevie. Filling those shoes for 2 years Gary soon reformed a band of his own on the west coast with Dallas Bassist David Dennard creating Gary Myrick & the Figures. Myrick and band released his first album in 1980 garnering the hit “she talks in stereo” making top one hundred of the decade on kroq radio and the song was used in film soundtracks.Myrick after touring and gaining many great reviews and reputation decided to go full solo releasing Language with 2 hits “guitar talk love and drums and more from that record.Myrick soon also worked writing and playing guitar on a band project with John Waite garnering the grammy nominated song Missing You with a billboard chart of number 1. My left the project after its release to make his 4th album “Stand for love”. Not pleased with his record company pared up with Paul Simonon of The Clash to start a band called Havana 3AM bring his Texas upbringing into the sound,making number 4 in the Rolling Stone alternative chart. A world tour later and the sad passing for his singer Nigel Dixon created a new follow up Gary Myrick and Havana 3am,texas glitter and tombstone tales ,whose songs were used in 3 film soundtracks.Myrick also during this period wrote a all acoustic album “Waltz of the Scarecrow King on a Indie label.

event.description: It will be a whole night of nothing but absolute shred fest. Come on out to see all of these incredible musicians shredding faces off! Desiree' Bassett: Throughout the years, she has performed with many outstanding and renowned musicians including Living Colour, Andy Aledort, Geraldo Velez, Jeff Baxter “Skunk”, members of the Allman Brothers Band, Sammy Hagar, Ted Nugent Marshall Tucker Band, Foghat, Barry Goudreau (formerly of the band Boston), and many more. With the explosion of the social media world, Desiree quickly became world-known through videos of her performances on MySpace, Facebook and YouTube. Desiree’ currently has 3 albums out (Power & Force, Power & Force II and A Bit Above) and has gone through a few tours: -Cirque du Soleil’s Michael Jackson the IMMORTAL World Tour (2011-2014) which featured some of Michael Jackson’s original band members and has gone around 27 different countries in 141 cities with over 500 performances, hitting the box offices of being the 7th highest grossing tour of over $374 million. -Blue Moon Tour with world renowned drummer Stacey Lamont Sydnor and world famous bassist Linley Marthe that took place in Europe in 4 different countries. -Jane Zhang's Bang The World Concert that featured two concerts in Jane’s hometown Chengdu, China. One concert featuring a very electrifying show of dance, pop, and electronic and another concert Jane Zhang and Friends that performed with a 90 piece orchestra and had featured world famous artists such as Chris Botti and John Legend. -The Legacy Tour featuring William Hall that is a totally dedicated, emotionally powerful driven show that tributes to the all time favorite Michael Jackson. The tour took place in Australia from May – July of 2016 and August – October of 2017 and Germany from September – October of 2016 and is still currently touring around the world. Currently, Desiree’ still continues to tour around the world while on her time off works on her 4th album and performs shows with her band Desiree' & the Time Machine, a power trio that features her on lead guitar and vocals, Robert Gottfried on drums and Bob Laramie on bass, and a side project she occasionally performs with known as Siksay Band. Shadow Eden: Shadow Eden creates music that dazzles with virtuosity, ignites the senses, and pushes boundaries. Shadow Eden culminates the heralded talents of founding members David Mercado & drummer Kenny Lane, who joined by bassist extraordinaire Randy Coven in 2011 quickly became a mainstay of the Northeast circuit. Shadow Eden's self titled, self-financed and promoted ALL instrumental release, entered the regular rotation of national college radio stations entering the top 40 on the CMJ charts !! Shadow Eden began work on it's release in the Summer of 2013. "Perpetual Motion," was completed in March of 2014 and soon thereafter the band began making preparations for a Summer release, which was tragically derailed by the untimely passing of Randy Coven. Confronted by overwhelming odds and pressure, in the face of the pending release, the band held auditions for a replacement. A fan of both Shadow Eden & The Mark Wood Experience introduced them to Mark Wood's bass player, Paul Ranieri. Ranieri, a masterful musician & Bass player, was the perfect fit for the musical pedigree of Shadow Eden, officially joining the band in July of 2014. Since it's founding in 2009, Shadow Eden has enjoyed great fortune, being propelled to the forefront of their genre by sheer musical prowess & determination, earning them the respect of their contemporaries and gaining them legions of new fans. In the words of The Metal Fields Kerb Vater, " People who are interested in good instrumental work should give Shadow Eden a listen...." A new chapter now begins....Dave, Paul & Claudio Joe Stump: Joe Stump (born September 18 , 1960) is an American guitarist and composer. He plays neo-classical metal, in a style similar to that of Yngwie Malmsteen. He has released albums with his band, Reign of Terror and as a solo artist. Stump is a professional shredder, and Guitar One Magazine voted him 6th position among the Top 10 fastest shredders of all time. Stump has taught for many years at the Berklee College of Music in Boston. He also plays the lead guitar for the symphonic metal band HolyHell

event.description: Seattle Trance Alliance Presents: Will Atkinson While others are restrained by genre association Will Atkinson runs free, refusing to confirm or be pigeonholed. Is he tech, trance, techno, electronica, progressive, experimental.....? He is all of them and so much more. And its tthis ambidextrous Talent that has been the driving foforce behind Wills vast appeal and subsequent ever-growing army of passionate fans the world over. The video for his recent single DzPat Butcherdz (Beatportnumber 1 for 3 weeks) generated 1.6 million views in 48 hours so to say this exciting young uber talent is on fire right now, would be something of an understatement. Will Atkinson is an entity that congers up futuristic soundscapes for the jilted generation. Responsible for over 100 BBC Radio 1airplays and 6 Beatport number 1s the kid that began mixing records at the age of 7 has certainly come of age. Its no wonder therefore that with this level of hype that the BBC have now asked Will to join their illustrious Radio 1 line up, as one of their new residents presentinga series of monthly shows that kick off in July of this year. Wills discography is quite simply a long list of hit records. DzPat Butcherdz, DzVictimsdz, DzNumb The Paindz, DzSubconsciousdz, DzMesmerizedz (ft Rowetta from The Happy Mondays), DzThe Gamer Changerdz, DzFresh Meatdz....... all genre defining, chart topping, iconic titles that set the bar uncomfortably high for Wills peers to try and follow. Having released on all of the scenes coolest labels including Subculture, Kearnage, FSOE, Spinnin, Armada, Perfecto Fluoro and Vandit - the demand for Wills production skills is truly rampant. His tour schedule reads like a catalogue of the coolest festivals and clubs in the world with a residency at Cream Ibiza 2016 and regular peak time slots at EDC Vegas, EDC Mexico, Dreamstate all over the US, Beyond Wonderland, Creamfields, Luminosity, BAT Buenos Aires, Subculture Australia, Earthcore, ASOT and many more. Today Will joins the elite VII collective to launch a brand new record label that promises topush the boundaries of cutting edge electronic insanity. His monthly Mainline Radio show is fast becoming a soundcloud sensation with tens of thousands of loyal listeners tuning in each month to hear whats hot in Wills world.....At long last a new headliner of genuine substance and quality is born. I love Will's tracks and have been playing many of them in my DJ sets and radio shows. He's one of the best artists out there!Armin van Buuren A pioneer, unique super talent making the freshest music in our scene. Everything Will makes is razor sharp cutting edge.Simon Patterson Will is an extremely rare talent that only comes along every 10 years or so. No one can touch him right now when it comes to trance and tech trance" John OCallaghan Will is so forward thinking with his music. He always manages to create something unique that sounds like nothing else out there. Sean Tyas Wills music is off the chain. Its so refreshing and exciting. Hes a true genius both on the decks and in the studio. John Askew 21+ The Underground 122 S Washington St Seattle WA 98104

Doors open at 7pm

Price at the door - 21 & up - $8, 18-20 - $15

No refunds on purchased tickets.

The Big Texas Next Up series brings you up and coming Texas and regional artists at a reduced ticket price.  Come see which artists will be the "Next Up" to make it big.

Event Description:
You are cordially invited to a cocktail attire dinner and exclusive concert event to benefit your Lafayette Symphony! The evening will feature cocktail hour and an elegant dinner at Carnahan Hall with musical entertainment by the Abel Duo and the Randy Salman Jazz Band. Leave your checkbook at home- there will be no auctions, raffles, or solicitations at the event although a full bar will be provided. **Cash & Card Accepted** Simply relax and enjoy this one of a kind experience only your LSO can provide. RSVP IS REQUIRED BY 9/17/18 Tickets available for purchase on LSO's website!

LOCATION: Carnahan Hall
